 athletes competing in the Olympics go through more frequent testing compared to athletes from other countries.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978577301190765, \"rank\": 0.0019387730099619817, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Records\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"more frequent testing\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2191}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2212}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While each Chinese swimmer is tested 21 times on average in the lead up to the Paris Games, the number is six for the Americans, five for the Italians and four for Australians according to data from World Aquatics, a governing body recognized by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978577301190765, \"rank\": 0.0019387730099619817, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2485, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"average\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2337}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"the Italians\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2385}, {\"ngram\": \"Australians\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2448}, {\"ngram\": \"a governing body\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most importantly, they also compete clean with 0.2 percent of doping violations detected in 2022, which is significantly lower than the U.S. and Canada, according to data by WADA.\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2664, \"end\": 2670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999539237662048, \"rank\": 4.604334065178517e-05, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"0.2 percent\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"doping violations\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2598}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2697}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prejudice and injustice against Chinese athletes at international sporting events have infuriated many, including Chinese swimmer Zhang Yufei who questioned why athletes such as Phelps have not faced the same scrutiny when he shattered records and won eight gold medals in a single Olympic event.\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978577301190765, \"rank\": 0.0019387730099619817, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2814, \"end\": 2821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978577301190765, \"rank\": 0.0019387730099619817, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2830, \"end\": 2841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9727864122994488, \"rank\": 0.027972027972036382, \"text\": \"Zhang Yufei\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2878, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999992742232, \"rank\": 7.254358088921745e-10, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Prejudice\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"injustice\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"international sporting events\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2781}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2869}, {\"ngram\": \"the same scrutiny\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2917}, {\"ngram\": \"records\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2943}, {\"ngram\": \"eight gold medals\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2969}, {\"ngram\": \"a single Olympic event\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 2995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zhang, who participated in this year's Paris Olympics, pointed out that Chinese athletes already go through a rigorous if not tedious testing process for banned substances by official agencies such as WADA.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\"